<section xmlns="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook" xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink" version="5.0" xml:id="FAM001SEQUEN_001">
    <title>Sequences of AED instructions</title>
    <subtitle role="chapterTitle">how to use an AED</subtitle>
    <para>The AED will start to give you a series of visual and verbal prompts as soon as it is switched on. There are several difference AED models available, seach of which has different voice prompts. You should always follow the prompts given by the aED that you are using until advanced emergency care is available.
    </para>
    <section role="flowchart" xml:id="FAM001FLOWCH_001">
        <title/>
        <info>
            <extendedlink>
                <locator xlink:href="FAM001FLOWCH_004" xlink:label="AED_switch_on"/>
                <locator xlink:href="FAM001FLOWCH_005" xlink:label="AED_ready_analyze"/>
                <locator xlink:href="FAM001FLOWCH_006" xlink:label="AED_shock_needed"/>
