        <section role="flowchart_step" xml:id="FAM001FLOWCH_004">
          <title/>
            <itemizedlist mark="bullet">
                <listitem>
                    <para>Switch AED on.</para>
                </listitem>
                <listitem>
                    <para>Attach pads to casualty's chest.</para>
                </listitem>
            </itemizedlist>
        </section>

        <section role="flowchart_step" xml:id="FAM001FLOWCH_005">
            <title/>
            <para>AED gets ready to analyse the casualty's heart rhythm. It may state "Stand clear, analysing now" or "Analysing". Make sure that no-one is touching the casualty.</para>
            <para role="flowchart_question">Is a shock advised?</para>
       </section>

        <section role="flowchart_step" xml:id="FAM001FLOWCH_006">
        <title/>
           <para>AED advised that a shock is needed.</para>
           <para>The machines charges up.</para>
        </section>

        <section role="flowchart_step" xml:id="FAM001FLOWCH_007">
            <title/>
            <para>AED instructs you to deliver the shock.</para>
            <itemizedlist mark="bullet">
                <listitem>
                    <para>Make sure that everyone is clear of the casualty.</para>
                </listitem>
                <listitem>
                    <para>Push the shock button.</para>
                </listitem>
            </itemizedlist>
            <para>AED delivers the shock. The casualty will appear to "jump" with each shock. This is quite normal.</para>
        </section>

        <section role="flowchart_step" xml:id="FAM001FLOWCH_008">
            <title/>
            <para>AED instructs you to carry out chest compressions and rescue breath (CPR) 30:2 for two minutes before it re-analyses.</para>
         </section>


        <section role="flowchart_step" xml:id="FAM001FLOWCH_009">
            <title/>
        <para>The AED re-analyses heart rhythm.</para>
        <itemizedlist mark="bullet">
            <listitem>
                <para>If at any time the casualty starts breathing normally, place him in the recovery position (pp 64-65). Leave the AED attached to the casualty.</para>
            </listitem>
        </itemizedlist>
        </section>
        
        <section role="flowchart_step" xml:id="FAM001FLOWCH_010">
            <title/>
            <para>AED advises that no shock is needed.</para>
        </section>   
        
        <section role="flowchart_step" xml:id="FAM001FLOWCH_011">
            <title/>
            <para>AED instructs you to carry out chest compressions and rescue breath (CPR) 30:2 for two minutes before it re-analyses heart rhythm.</para>
        </section>
        
        <section role="flowchart_step" xml:id="FAM001FLOWCH_012">
            <title/>
            <para>The AED re-analyses heart rhythm.</para>
        </section>

    </section>   
</section>






